<p><span class="speaker">Unidentified participant</span>Mr. Faulkner, I believe Somerset Maugham said at one time that he felt it
                    was rather a sad thing in his own life and assumed it to be in the life of any
                    writer in that he felt that he had to divorce himself from life itself, to a
